13:49.691 --> 13:52.361
Have all your metal fillings
been removed, sir? Yeah.

13:54.363 --> 13:56.782
The machine is a giant magnet.

13:57.491 --> 14:00.077
Any metal will
disrupt the process.

14:00.160 --> 14:01.800
So you're sure we're
not missing anything?

14:02.806 --> 14:04.095
Good.

14:11.463 --> 14:12.613
One, two...

14:24.643 --> 14:25.852
What's that?

14:29.731 --> 14:31.051
It's something to
stop your heart.

14:31.650 --> 14:32.800
What?

14:33.151 --> 14:35.571
I said it's something
to stop your heart.

15:30.542 --> 15:31.918
It didn't work.

15:40.927 --> 15:42.304
- It didn't work.
- What's your name?

15:42.387 --> 15:43.537
It didn't...

15:45.098 --> 15:46.266
It didn't work.

15:46.892 --> 15:48.435
What's your name?

15:49.603 --> 15:50.937
Damian.

15:54.566 --> 15:55.734
Damian.

16:50.831 --> 16:54.167
It will take a few days,
but it gets easier.

16:55.961 --> 17:00.048
It has that new body smell.

17:15.313 --> 17:16.463
<i>Damian.</i>

17:21.319 --> 17:23.446
- Damian?
- Yeah?

17:23.530 --> 17:25.824
- Are you all right?
- Yes.

17:29.536 --> 17:32.038
Death has some side effects.

17:33.373 --> 17:36.418
Here. The paper of record.

17:39.880 --> 17:42.424
We can arrange
a visit to the plot

17:42.507 --> 17:45.302
in a few months if it
holds any significance.

17:47.137 --> 17:49.514
But right now...

17:53.727 --> 17:55.270
Get some rest if you can.

17:58.398 --> 18:00.692
Tomorrow's your
first day of school.

19:10.554 --> 19:13.473
So, how are you feeling?

19:14.266 --> 19:17.477
Terrific. I have the physical
dexterity of a toddler.

19:17.853 --> 19:19.604
Two hundred and
fifty million well spent.

19:19.688 --> 19:22.232
A sense of humor. Good.

19:22.899 --> 19:27.696
It's important actually.
Helps to fend off despair.

19:27.779 --> 19:29.531
Is that why I'm only
allowed plastic knives?

19:30.073 --> 19:32.242
Suicidal thoughts
are not uncommon.

19:32.325 --> 19:36.663
Inhabiting a body the mind regards
as alien can be pretty overwhelming.

19:39.499 --> 19:43.420
- And what is that? Prozac?
- No, not exactly. No.

19:43.503 --> 19:46.006
The "glitches" that
you've described to me?

19:46.089 --> 19:49.259
That's your mind adjusting
to its new neural structure.

19:49.342 --> 19:52.888
And you can expect occasional, mild
hallucinations for the first year.

19:53.013 --> 19:54.556
Jesus. There's nothing
to worry about.

19:54.639 --> 19:57.058
Think of it as
the anti-rejection drug

19:57.183 --> 19:59.603
that you'd take
after any transplant.

19:59.686 --> 20:01.688
And what does
rejection look like?

20:01.771 --> 20:05.775
Well, migraine, nausea,
disorientation, and then...

20:06.234 --> 20:08.320
- Well, death.
- Oh.

20:09.279 --> 20:11.823
Is that all?
An irrelevant hypothetical.

20:11.907 --> 20:14.117
- One a day for the time being.
- Hell yes.

